een Bay To Launch USL League Two Club In 2019|date=October 27, 2018|publisher=USL League Two|accessdate=October 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| [[Ashwaubenon, Wisconsin]]\n| [[Capital Credit Union Park]]\n| align=center | 2018\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Brian Kamler]]\n|-\n| [[Kaw Valley FC]]\n| [[Lawrence, Kansas]]/[[Topeka, Kansas]]\n| Rock Chalk Park/Humner Sports Park\n| align=center | 2017\n| {{flagicon|HUN}} [[Istv\u00e1n Urb\u00e1nyi]]\n|-\n| [[FC Manitoba]]\n| [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]]\n| [[Ralph Cantafio Soccer Complex]]\n| align=center | 2010\n| {{flagicon|ROU}} Eduardo Badescu\n|-\n| [[Peoria, Illinois|Peoria City]]\n| [[Peoria, Illinois]]\n| [[Shea Stadium (Peoria, Illinois)|Shea Stadium]]\n| align=center | 2020\n| \n|-\n| [[St. Louis Lions]]\n| [[St. Louis, Missouri]]\n| Tony Glavin Soccer Complex\n| align=center | 2006\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Tony Glavin]]\n|-\n| [[Thunder Bay Chill]]\n| [[Thunder Bay, Ontario]]\n| [[Fort William Stadium]]\n| align=center | 2000\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} Giovanni Petraglia\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:left; background:gray;\" | <span style=\"color:white;\">Mid South Division</span>\n|-\n| [[AHFC Royals]]\n| [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n| Campbell Road Sports Park\n| align=center | 2017\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Josh Gardner (soccer)|Josh Gardner]]\n|-\n| [[Brazos Valley Cavalry F.C.]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.houstondynamo.com/post/2017/01/16/premier-development-league-soccer-headed-brazos-valley| title=Premier Development League Soccer Headed to the Brazos Valley |publisher=Houston Dynamo |date=January 16, 2017 | accessdate=January 26, 2017}}</ref>\n| [[Bryan, Texas]]\n| [[Nutrabolt Stadium]]\n| align=center | 2017\n| James Clarkson\n|-\n| [[Corpus Christi FC]]\n| [[Corpus Christi, Texas]]\n| [[Texas A&M\u2013Corpus Christi Islanders|Dugan Stadium]]\n| align=center | 2017\n| {{flagicon|COL}} Sebastian Giraldo\n|-\n| [[Houston FC]]\n| [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n| [[Houston Baptist Huskies|Sorrels Field]]\n| align=center | 2017\n| {{